1. Separate Facts / Inferences / Assumptions.
2. Start with bear case first, then base, then bull.
3. If you can’t verify a figure, write Unknown and list the exact doc/source to check (10-K, 10-Q, earnings deck, transcript).
4. Provide a final checklist of 10 items I should validate manually.
5. Avoid hype language; be specific.
6. If you want, tell me your investor persona (e.g., “US large-cap quality, 3–5y, avoid loss-making, okay with tech”) and I’ll also create a single mega-prompt that produces a consistent one-page “research note” every time you paste a ticker.</pre>
