4. ROIC (or ROE/ROA where ROIC not meaningful) + trend
5. Dilution: shares outstanding + SBC trend (3Y) + net buybacks
6. Factor tagging (must label each stock): Quality / Value / Momentum / Low Vol / Growth / Dividend / Cyclical

Valuation (required):
- Relative: vs peer group + vs its own history (e.g., 5Y range/median)
- Include 2–3 multiples relevant to the business (PE, EV/EBITDA, EV/FCF, P/S, FCF yield).

Output format:
1. Ranked table (Top 20) with: ticker, sector, market cap bucket, rev growth, EBIT/FCF margin, ROIC, net debt/EBITDA, FCF yield, SBC %, buyback %, valuation vs peers, factor tag, 1-line thesis
2. Top 5 deep dives: bull/base/bear thesis, key KPIs to track, and 3 catalysts (12–18m)
3. Reject list (10): what disqualified them (e.g., valuation too stretched, weak cash conversion, high dilution)

Rules: separate facts vs assumptions; if data is missing, mark Unknown and list what to verify.`
