- Marketplace: take rate, GMV growth, cohorts, contribution margin
- Consumer/platform: engagement, monetization, ad load, TAC, ARPU, churn
- Industrial/retail: volume, price, utilization, same-store sales, inventory turns

B) Forecast model (5 years):
- Revenue drivers (explicit) + margin bridge (gross → operating)
- Reinvestment: capex, working capital, R&D capitalization if relevant
- SBC treatment: show value impact via dilution (share count path) and/or expense normalization (state approach)

C) Cost of capital:
- WACC assumptions and justification (Rf, ERP, beta, size/sector adjustments if used)
- Terminal value using BOTH perpetuity and exit multiple (justify multiple with comps)

D) Sensitivities (must):
- WACC × terminal growth
- Revenue CAGR × operating margin
- Optional: churn / take-rate / utilization sensitivity (depending on business)

Output:
1. Valuation range (bear/base/bull) + implied IRR from current price
2. “5 break assumptions” that would invalidate the base case
3. 10-item diligence checklist (what to verify in filings / investor decks)`
            },
